TITLE: US officials warn of uptick in weapons smuggled to Haiti
SUMMARY: U.S. investigators say they've spotted an uptick in the amount and caliber of weapons being smuggled from Florida to Haiti in recent months

TITLE: Appeals rulings at odds over Confederate-themed jury room
SUMMARY: Two Black men who challenged their criminal convictions after jurors deliberated in a Tennessee courthouse room containing Confederate symbols have received opposite rulings from different judges on the same appeals court

TITLE: US says SkyWest employee subjected to sexual harassment
SUMMARY: Federal officials are suing SkyWest Airlines on behalf of a former employee who says she was subjected to sexual harassment by co-workers, included asking her for sex and making explicit comments about rape in her presence

TITLE: Companies plan $2.6B investment in major Alaska oil project
SUMMARY: Two oil and gas companies have announced plans to invest $2.6 billion into developing a major oil field on Alaska’s North Slope

TITLE: Parole granted to last 1976 California school bus hijacker
SUMMARY: The last of three men convicted of hijacking a school bus full of California children for an attempted $5 million ransom in 1976 is being released by the state’s parole board

TITLE: Evidence dispute spills into public in Alex Murdaugh case
SUMMARY: Attorneys for disbarred South Carolina lawyer Alex Murdaugh say prosecutors are taking too much time to share their evidence that the disbarred attorney killed his wife and son

TITLE: Kemp's ridley sea turtle nests 1st in 75 years in Louisiana
SUMMARY: The world's smallest and most endangered sea turtle has hatched in Louisiana's wilds for the first known time in 75 years

TITLE: Concerns over segregation display led to post office closure

SUMMARY: A Wisconsin school board has voted in favor of a policy that prohibits teachers and staff from displaying gay pride flags and other items that district officials consider political in nature

SUMMARY: A hermit who was evicted from New Hampshire property on which he had lived for nearly three decades has found a new home in Maine

SUMMARY: The attorneys for Florida school shooter Nikolas Cruz won't present to his jurors the results of a controversial test that they said supports their belief he suffers from fetal alcohol syndrome

TITLE: Iowa council member countersues police over protest arrest
SUMMARY: A Des Moines council member is countersuing two police officers who took the unusual step earlier this year of suing several people who participated in a 2020 protest following a Minneapolis officer’s killing of George Floyd

TITLE: Prosecutors seek death penalty in Indiana officer's slaying
SUMMARY: Prosecutors are seeking the death penalty for a man accused of fatally shooting a young Indiana police officer last month during an early morning traffic stop

TITLE: Man's mental health questioned in Vegas airport panic case
SUMMARY: A defense attorney raised questions Wednesday about the mental health of his client, a 33-year-old California man accused of causing panic early Sunday during his second arrest in two days at busy Harry Reid International Airport in Las Vegas

TITLE: Texas to execute man for slaying of Dallas real estate agent
SUMMARY: A man who fatally stabbed a real estate agent inside a model home in suburban Dallas faces execution, more than 16 years after the slaying

TITLE: R. Kelly lawyer implores jurors at trial on child porn, other charges not to accept portrayal of singer as `a monster'
SUMMARY: R. Kelly lawyer implores jurors at trial on child porn, other charges not to accept portrayal of singer as `a monster'

TITLE: UN special envoy to Myanmar urges immediate halt to violence
SUMMARY: The U.N. special envoy for Myanmar, Noeleen Heyzer, has met with the head of its military-installed government and urged a halt to all violence on her first visit to the strife-torn country

SUMMARY: Prosecutors plan to seek the death penalty for a Las Vegas man accused of killing his girlfriend’s 4-year-old son and hiding the body in a freezer

TITLE: US retail sales were flat in July as inflation takes a toll
SUMMARY: The pace of sales at U.S. retailers was unchanged last month.

TITLE: Miami officer still critical as robbery suspect identified
SUMMARY: Police in South Florida say a 29-year-old officer remains in “extremely critical condition" after being shot in the head during a confrontation with a robbery suspect in Miami

TITLE: China and US spar over climate on Twitter
SUMMARY: The world’s two biggest emitters of greenhouse gases are sparring on Twitter.

TITLE: Pakistani doctor pleads guilty to terror charge in Minnesota
SUMMARY: A Pakistani doctor and former Mayo Clinic research coordinator has pleaded guilty to a terrorism charge, more than two years after he was arrested for telling paid FBI informants that he pledged his allegiance to the Islamic State group
